Description: Fragment of double handle from a Koan pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine red-brown; some mica; mixed inclusions. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Isidoros. Unpublished parallel in Athenian Agora. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 173, 6.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0131)
